{
  "brand": "Sharp",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "Sharp XV / PG / Notevision series (ASCII 8-byte command protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: Sharp Notevision PG-F212X / PG-F255W / XG-V10X / XV-Z2000 RS232 operation manuals.",
    "Wire: D-Sub 9-pin cross-over. 9600 8N1 (some models also support 115200), no flow control.",
    "Format: 4-char command + 4-char parameter (right-justified, space-padded) + CR (0x0D). Total 9 bytes.",
    "Example: 'POWR   1' + CR sets power on. The 4-character parameter is space-padded on the left.",
    "Projector replies with 'OK<CR>' on success or 'ERR<CR>' on failure (4 bytes + CR).",
    "Query commands use '?' as the parameter (right-justified, padded). Responses: POWR? -> '0' (off) / '1' (on). TLPT? -> 4-digit lamp hours (0000-9999). TLPS? -> '0' (OK) / '1' (replace soon) / '2' (replace now) / '3' (lamp out). IMVL? -> remaining lamp life percentage. AVMT? -> '0' (off) / '1' (on). VOLA? -> 0-60 volume. IMOD? -> current input source (RGB/DVI/VID/SVD)."
  ],
